Run 'bundle install' to get Gems - however, seems to be a bug with sauce/selenium that bundle exec ruby ts_web doesn't work.

Screenshots
 Screenshots are generated after every failure to the output/ directory

Waiting after failure
 export SAUCE_SLEEP_ON_FAILURE=<number of seconds after each failure>

Running local tests
 export LOCAL_SELENIUM=1
 export SAUCE_BROWSER_URL=https://<host>/app
 ruby ts_web

Running an individual test
 export LOCAL_SELENIUM=1
 export SAUCE_BROWSER_URL=https://<host>/app
 ruby -rubygems testcases/tc_console.rb -n test_ssh_keys

 (some individual tests have not been converted - if you get an error about undefined constants be sure to add the correct requires)
